headline: Agilent’s (NYSE:A) Q4 Sales Top Estimates But Full-Year Sales Guidance Misses Expectations
summary: Life sciences tools company Agilent Technologies (NYSE:A) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2024, with sales up 1.4% year on year to $1.68 billion. On the other hand, next quarter’s revenue guidance of $1.63 billion was less impressive, coming in 1.4% below analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $1.11 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Agilent Reports First-Quarter Fiscal Year 2025 Financial Results
summary: SANTA CLARA, Calif., February 26, 2025--Agilent Technologies Inc. (NYSE: A) today reported revenue of $1.68 billion for the first quarter ended Jan. 31, 2025, representing growth of 1.4% reported and up 1.2% core(1) compared to the first quarter of 2024.
